{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2d603253-05ed-4165-89bb-9919c527d867","content":"Use `dotnet watch` to automatically re-run tests on every file save:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"RemoveStock_ExceedsAvailable_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis watches for changes to `InventoryServiceTests.cs` (or any source file), rebuilds, and reruns only that test.\n\n**Quick diagnosis of your failing test:** `RemoveStock` silently subtracts without checking availability. It needs a guard:\n\n```csharp\npublic void RemoveStock(string sku, int quantity)\n{\n    var current = _stock.GetValueOrDefault(sku);\n    if (quantity > current)\n        throw new InvalidOperationException(\"Insufficient stock\");\n    _stock[sku] = current - quantity;\n}\n```\n\nWant me to apply that fix and run the tests?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"de65a7f6-ebc5-4530-9c61-223cf37a8025","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up hot reload for their test project. Since this is using .NET 10 with Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner, they can use `dotnet test --hotreload` or `dotnet watch test`. Let me check what's available.\n\nActually, with .NET and Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the best option for hot reload testing is `dotnet watch`. The command would be:\n\n```\ndotnet watch test --filter \"RemoveStock_ExceedsAvailable_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will watch for file changes and automatically re-run the tests.\n\nLet me just tell them how to do it. They asked \"how can I set up hot reload\" — this is an advice question more than a \"do it for me\" question.","outputTokens":379,"requestId":"0830:1DCDBF:7F11DB9:8DA154B:69EAC816"},"id":"87962028-84de-46a4-8237-d09021afa157","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:32:15.646Z","parentId":"f6c99cf1-f596-438c-a2ae-537ac54a9fca"}
